Function Reference/get the category rss « WordPress Codex
-----------

Retrieve all of the post categories, formatted for use in feeds.

All of the categories for the current post in the feed loop, will be
retrieved and have feed markup added, so that they can easily be added
to the RSS2, Atom, or RSS1 and RSS0.91 RDF feeds.

Usage
-----

` <?php get_the_category_rss( $type ); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$type` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) default is '`rss`'. Either '`rss`', '`atom`', or
    '`rdf`'.
    Default: 'rss'

Return Values
-------------

 (string) 
:   All of the post categories for displaying in the feed.

Examples
--------

Notes
-----

-   Uses:
    [`apply_filters()`](/Function_Reference/apply_filters "Function Reference/apply filters")

Change Log
----------

Since: 2.1.0

Source File
-----------

`get_the_category_rss()` is located in `wp-includes/feed.php`.

